WaterDragFunction - Class in com.sailing.math.functions
D = 1/2 * p * C(beta) * V^2 * S
Where:
D = drag
p = water density
C(beta) = drag coefficient in respect to beta
beta = angle of attack
V = boat velocity
S = centerboard area
==> roh * (m/s)^2 * m^2 = (kg/m^3) * (m/s)^2 * m^2 = (kg * m^2 * m^2) / (m^3 * s^2) = kg * m / s^2 = N
